Analysis on the relationship between the Sea Dispersal Potential index and morphological traits of Gal√°pagos littoral plants

Script description

  1. Testing the relationship between morphological traits related to thalassochory plus additional diaspore features (fleshiness, shape and size) and the SDPi.

1.1. Mann‚ÄìWhitney‚ÄìWilcoxon tests performed to analyze whether SDPi values differ between species classified as thalassochorous vs.¬†non-thalassochorous 1.2. Linear Models fitted to analyse the relationship between shape and size of diaspores and the SDPi values.

Transformation - Tukey‚Äôs Ladder of Powers

transformTukey() function performs iterative Shapiro‚ÄìWilk tests, and finds the lambda value that maximizes the W statistic from those tests. In essence, this finds the power transformation that makes the data fit the normal distribution as closely as possible with this type of transformation.

###SDP index t33h
SDP33_Tuk<-transformTukey(df$SDP_t33) #Lambda = 0.9

if (lambda >  0){TRANS = x ^ lambda} 
if (lambda == 0){TRANS = log(x)} 
if (lambda <  0){TRANS = -1 * x ^ lambda} 

###SDP index t21d
